# PXELINUX Legacy BIOS Bootloader Stub
# This file serves as a placeholder for the actual pxelinux.0 bootloader
# In production, replace this with the real pxelinux.0 from SYSLINUX project
# Location: https://www.syslinux.org/wiki/index.php/PXELINUX
# 
# Real deployment: Download from https://mirrors.kernel.org/syslinux/
# Copy the actual binary to replace this file
#
# Boot Mode: Legacy BIOS/MBR
# Partition Table: MBR
# File System: Any (NTFS, ext4, etc.)
# Compatibility: Maximum - works with older systems
#
# BIOS PXE Boot Flow:
# 1. Device sends DHCP DISCOVER
# 2. DHCP server responds with bootfile: pxelinux.0
# 3. Device fetches pxelinux.0 via TFTP
# 4. pxelinux.0 loads pxelinux.cfg/default configuration
# 5. Configuration specifies kernel/image to load
# 6. Image deployment begins via HTTP/NFS/iSCSI
